Add assertions in Command and Nyx classes
commitResults.messageBody:
The Command and Nyx classes lack state validations through assertions.
This may propagate into an invalid state, impacting reliability.
Let's add assertions to the Command and Nyx classes. This change
enforces critical conditions during execution, improving early error
detection.
These targeted assertions help to catch unexpected behaviour early
during development.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add spacing to improve logical structure Add more comments for readability Refactor Parser to use switch
commitResults.messageBody:
Parser.java exhibits a long chain of if/else statements that reduce
readability and clarity. Some files also lack sufficient comments,
which obscures the intent behind some design decisions.

A refactoring is essential to improve maintainability and ease of
comprehension. Let's add spacing to visually separate code sections,
replace if/else chains with a switch statement to streamline logic,
and add comments to clarify the purpose of critical code segments.

Using a switch statement produces a more organized structure, while
readability improvements and comments help future developers understand
the code with minimal effort.
